mstSvtCostume.costumeReleaseDetail: Acquire the Wardrobe Key for Spiritron Dress "Grey Collar"

mstItem.name: Mystic Spinal Fluid
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
A potion to turn an ordinary human into a mage. When injected into the spine, it creates temporary artificial Magical Circuits.

mstItem.name: Mysterious Divine Wine
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
This precious wine was brewed over a long period of time to be offered to the gods. It can intoxicate even monsters and demonic beasts.

mstItem.name: Stake of Wailing Night
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
A stake driven into a corpse to prevent its reanimation.
It never rusts, and retains its luster by absorbing blood.
It can even pierce otherworldly beings that lurk in the dark of night.

mstItem.name: Mystic Gunpowder
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
Custom made gunpowder that ignites when the user focuses magical energy into it.
Since it can generate a massive amount of firepower with only a small amount of magical energy, it's widely utilized as ammunition to hunt Demonic Beasts.

mstItem.name: Eternal Ice
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
Ice that does not melt, even at room temperature.
Some see a lovely crystalline flower, but those with no appreciation of beauty see only a piece of ice.

mstItem.name: Egg of Truth
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
A sacred egg that is said to contain the truth of the world. Its shell is so tough that no being can break it.

mstItem.name: Secret Gem of Archer
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up Material"
A bright stone glimmering with the immense power of an Archer.

mstItem.name: Archer Monument
mstItem.detail:
"Ascension Material"
A monument in glory of the Archer class.

mstItem.name: Holy Grail
mstItem.detail:
A container said to grant any wish.
Created by the Third Magic, it is said 
that it can materialize those that do not possess forms.

mstItem.name: Magic Gem of Archer
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up Material"
A bright stone glimmering with the great power of an Archer.

mstItem.name: Crystallized Lore
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
A highly pure crystal of magic created
when human history crosses a stream of Mana.
It can be said that it is the ingredient for materializing Heroic Spirits.

mstItem.name: Archer Piece
mstItem.detail:
"Ascension Material"
A piece signifying the Archer class.

mstItem.name: Void's Dust
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
Dust that disperses when hollow shadows disappear.

mstItem.name: Claw of Chaos
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
Those wounded by this claw become prisoners of chaos.

mstItem.name: Forbidden Page
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
A page which nobody should ever read.
Usually mixed in as the first or last page.

mstItem.name: Servant Coin
mstItem.detail:
"Servant Enhancement Material"
 A shard of a Servant's Spirit Origin

mstItem.name: Gem of Archer
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up Material"
A bright stone glimmering with the power of an Archer.

mstItem.name: Tearstone of Blood
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
The crystal of the tear shed by a giant eyeball-like creature when it dies.
A strong curse is residing within this crystal.

mstItem.name: Scarab of Wisdom
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
A sacred ornament that symbolizes rebirth and regeneration.
Given only to the truly wise who can solve complex problems.

mstItem.name: Deadly Poisonous Needle
mstItem.detail:
"Skill Up & Ascension Material"
It is said that anyone who is infected by this poison will not die immediately, but experience multiple deaths until their soul itself rots away.

11.detail: A bartender's outfit with a butterfly motif. The Professor's fashion sense really shines through in this outfit.

mstSvtComment.comment:
Now, now, I am but an ordinary man!
Perhaps just the slightest bit craftier than most.
My magical bullets may be of some help to you... But do be careful, I only have so many!

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 1 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
Height/Weight: 175cm, 68kg
Origin: Sherlock Holmes Series
Region: All of Europe
Alignment: Chaotic-Evil
Gender: Male
Call me Mr. Dandy! (Not gonna happen)

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 2 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
A professor of mathematics and Sherlock Holmes's most formidable adversary.
Though he only appears in three books, usually as little more than a description offered by Holmes, this malevolently charismatic man enjoyed enormous support thanks to his machinations in Holmes's final (later made un-final) case.

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 3 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
A brilliant philosopher and certified genius.
Dubbed "The Napoleon of crime" by Holmes, he established a criminal network that spanned all of Europe while working as a professor of mathematics.
According to details revealed in the original books, he served as a kind of criminal consultant.

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 4 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
『The Dynamics of an Asteroid』
Rank: A+
NP Type: Anti-Army
Range: 1-99　Maximum Targets: 100
The Ultimate Crime.
A Noble Phantasm that manifests the ultimate destruction Moriarty seeks: that of the entire planet.
Though this NP remains at Anti-Army scale due to the limitations of the Servant container, it would expand to Anti-City and Anti-Nation if his power were to grow.

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlocks at Bond Level 5 after True Name revelation
mstSvtComment.comment:
A Fused Servant who has absorbed the Phantom Spirit "Der Freischütz," gaining his power to fire magic bullets.
In the play "The Marksman," a hunter sells his soul to the devil in exchange for six magic bullets that will always hit their target.
However, the seventh bullet will hit a target of the devil's own choosing... Someone whose death will plunge the hunter into despair.

mstSvtComment.condMessage: Unlock after completing "Seeking Quieter Times" and reach Bond Level 5
mstSvtComment.comment:
His lifelong rival is Sherlock Holmes.
Why does he get to be young and handsome while I'm stuck as a middle-aged gentleman? Why must I, a Servant, suffer chronic back pain!?
Holmes! Is... Could that be the power of baritsu?
Fine! As we are both aged gentlemen, I will ask the esteemed Li Shuwen to teach me a martial art!
No? Okay, I see...

infos.text:
[r]
You must be a peculiar Master to have summoned me!

[r]
My Class is Archer.[r]
For now, I shall hold off on revealing my True Name!

[id 202310_0_B050]True Name sealed. Pseudo Noble Phantasm, release.
[id 202310_0_B051]Time for your punishment!
[id 202310_0_B052]Wonderful... The world is full of destruction!
[id 202310_0_B053]Fwahahaha!
I shall accept.
It's an honor.
Let us begin. I must warm up, so kindly wait a moment!
Good. As a representative of the middle-aged Servants, I shall do my best.
Ack!? My hip! My hip just cracked!
Good. A flawless victory.
Ungh!
Impossible...!
We've come to a dead-end...
Sorry, but we need to retreat...
Jack...
Queen...
King...
Then, the Joker.
[id 202310_0_G010]Getting stronger is a good thing. Mhmm!
[id 202310_0_G020]Ah, so this is ascension. [id 202310_0_G021]Alas, I don't seem to have time for a wardrobe change.
[id 202310_0_G030]A wardrobe change. [id 202310_0_G031]I suppose such a thing isn't so exciting when it's an old man, though. [id 202310_0_G032]I assume you're in it for the skills. Am I correct?

[id 202310_0_G040]My wardrobe has become quite elaborate, my level has increased, [delay 3.8]and my back has started creaking. [id 202310_0_G041]But no! I'm fine! [id 202310_0_G042]I shall pay you back for raising me up to this point!
[id 202310_0_G050]I'm impressed you raised me up to this point without knowing my True Name! [id 202310_0_G051]What drew you to me? [id 202310_0_G052]Well, even I'm not rotten enough to betray you.
[id 202310_0_G9010]Getting stronger is a good thing. Mhmm!
Happy birthday! Youth fades in the blink of an eye. Enjoy it while you still can.
It seems there is an event going on right now. Are you going to participate?
All right. Shall we get going?
As your elder, I suppose my job is to show you the way. Mind you, I may lead you to evil.
Of course, you are an ace. No, no. I don't have anything up my sleeve. Really. Hahahaha.
Hm. I don't suppose this would give anything away... I love mathematics from the bottom of my heart. I find numbers soothing.
What I dislike...? Hahaha, let me think... What if I said deerstalker hats?
The Grail possesses great power, but that's all. It's no more or less than that, which makes it easy to account for in my calculations.
Let's work well together, Master!
True Names are not to be lightly revealed. That's how it goes.
What's wrong, Master? I will always be by your side.
...Do you like riddles? If you didn't, you wouldn't be raising a Servant who hasn't revealed his True Name up to this point.
Ah, you impress me. I cannot yet reveal my True Name, but I promise you that one day, I shall disclose it to you. I am a dishonest man, yes, but...well, that is the most I can think to say for now.

Is business good? Quite good!
Got that? So it's time to make a few exchanges!

Make your exchanges here!
Did you find the materials you sought?
No? My sincerest apologies.

Come to think of it, I'm probably the last person who would end up working an honest job.
Well anyway, keep on making those exchanges.

Shops of this nature tend to become intelligence swapping hotspots among villains. I suggest you keep an ear out while you gather your purchases.
Then again, you're my only customer!
My back is, well...you know. Could you help me out? Thanks a lot, Master.

Ah, so you've brought me this.
Very good, very good.
Time to change my profession to bartender.

The shop's about to close up.
But there's still time to make a few last-minute exchanges. Do so while you can.

These past few days were quite stimulating to me. Were they for you as well?
Entertainment is one of the crowning glories for villains. 
Well, see you next year. Take good care of whoever is keeping the shop then. It will not be me!

Welcome.
Heh heh heh. Calling me a pretty boy would be pushing it, and you will have to excuse my age. But there is no more refined gentleman than myself!
Anyway, do you have business in my shop?
How about a plastered statue of Napoleon? At least one of my wares is sure to please.

I'd like to open up my own shop when I retire.
Ah, but since I plan on being active for another half a century, that won't be for a while.
Anyway, do you have business here?

Wonderful.
What do you think of this Craft Essence?
I feel no small sense of pride in knowing how well it suits my Master.

Oh what a shame, the shop is closed.
The Red-Headed League has dissolved, and there will be no further business with Mister Garrideb.
But it's you and me we're talking about here; maybe we can sneak in an exchange.
"Auld Lang Syne" is about to play to signal the shop's closing time. Did you get everything you'd wanted? If not, you had best hurry.

Today is White Day, which means that all the effort you put in on Valentine's Day is finally going to pay off.
Maybe try asking Nursery Rhyme to summon a marshmallow creature for you?
At any rate, it looks like this year's going to be another tumultuous one.
But don't worry.
That's why we Servants are here for you... To cut through the thorny path before you.

Mystery invites further mystery. What goes around comes around, but the past is unchanging.
Care for a drink from the glass you brought me?
Would you care for whiskey? Gin? Or perhaps you just want oolong tea?

I'll show you that I can finish off ten steins before you can even finish your one drink.
The bet's off if either of us touch the others' glass.
If I can't beat you, I'll pay you a million yen. But I want a one stein head start.
...What would you do if I proposed a bet like that?
The answer should be...
Stay tuned tomorrow!

Now that you've given me a glass, here's the answer from last time:
What you should do is to hold on to your glass before you drink and just don't let go of it.
Hold it so that my stein won't cover up your glass.
But if I had a choice, I would just lose this bet graciously and simply raid the shop's vault later on.
After all, I have a feeling that the vault's quite stocked from this bet of ours!

The fourth glass.
In Asian nations, the number four is believed to be unlucky because it sounds like the word for "death," while the number thirteen is considered unlucky in the West.
But as such, evil villains like us quite embrace these numbers!
Huh? You don't consider yourself a villain?
Ah yes, I've forgotten about that.

Ah, your fifth glass? I'll take it.
If four's unlucky, then I guess five symbolizes stability.
Perhaps it is evocative of the five elements, or the Chinese concept of wuxing, or the five phases. Ah, and Friday is the fifth day of the week. It is certainly everyone's favorite, yes? All the better if work ends early that day.

We're finally at our sixth glass.
Six, six, six... Three sixes are even unluckier than thirteen.
It's the number of the Beast.
But of course, the numbers four, thirteen, and six hundred sixty-six are all mere numbers, mathematically speaking.
Well, humans do have a tendency to find beauty and terror in numbers.
If you are able to see past that, then maybe you'll be ready to call yourself a novice villain.

Let me take that last glass from you.
And here is your reward. Take it, now. Don't be shy.
Seven is seen as a lucky number, the number of fortune. But behind good fortune lies misfortune.
If you find yourself having this lucky number, don't let your guard down. There are those among us villains who take advantage of those seeking its good fortune.

Ah, so you've brought me this.
Very good, very good.
Time to change my profession to bartender.

Hahahaha!
You must be a peculiar Master to have summoned me!
My Class is Archer.
For now, I shall hold off on revealing my True Name!
But I am strong. That much I can guarantee!

A victory, Master. Let us toast to it.

No drinking and...dashing...
If I had only...hired a bouncer...

Kina Lillet.
Vesper Martini. Care for one?
